# Repository-wide line-ending normalization.
#
# Why: the runtime-index checksum validator
# (scripts/ai-skill-cli/internal/app/runtime.go::nativeRuntimeIndexChecksumsCheck)
# computes sha256 over raw file bytes. Without normalization, a Windows
# checkout with core.autocrlf=true produces CRLF content whose sha256 does
# not match the LF-content checksum stored in
# knowledge/runtime/sqlite/runtime-index.sqlite (refreshed on macOS/Linux).
# That divergence broke Windows CI starting at run 152.
#
# Forcing LF on text files at checkout (eol=lf) makes the validator
# portable without changing its semantics — no recomputation of stored
# checksums needed. After this file lands, Windows contributors should
# refresh their working tree once:
#     git rm --cached -r .
#     git reset --hard
# so checkout materializes LF endings.
#
# Binary file types are marked explicitly so Git stops trying to diff /
# normalize them. .sqlite / .db / .exe / .png / .pdf are the recurring
# ones in this repo.

# ── Text files: normalize to LF ─────────────────────────────────────────
*.md          text eol=lf
*.yaml        text eol=lf
*.yml         text eol=lf
*.json        text eol=lf
*.go          text eol=lf
*.py          text eol=lf
*.ts          text eol=lf
*.tsx         text eol=lf
*.js          text eol=lf
*.jsx         text eol=lf
*.sh          text eol=lf
*.bash        text eol=lf
*.toml        text eol=lf
*.txt         text eol=lf
*.csv         text eol=lf
*.tsv         text eol=lf
*.html        text eol=lf
*.css         text eol=lf
*.scss        text eol=lf
*.rb          text eol=lf
*.rs          text eol=lf
*.java        text eol=lf
*.kt          text eol=lf
*.swift       text eol=lf
go.mod        text eol=lf
go.sum        text eol=lf
Makefile      text eol=lf
*.mk          text eol=lf

# ── Binary files: do not normalize / diff as binary ─────────────────────
*.exe         binary
*.dll         binary
*.so          binary
*.dylib       binary
*.db          binary
*.sqlite      binary
*.sqlite3     binary
*.png         binary
*.jpg         binary
*.jpeg        binary
*.gif         binary
*.webp        binary
*.pdf         binary
*.zip         binary
*.gz          binary
*.tar         binary
*.tgz         binary
*.ico         binary
*.woff        binary
*.woff2       binary
*.ttf         binary
*.otf         binary
